{"tid":2274493,"cid":1,"subCid":0,"title":"國安法篤灰熱線現收到多過一千單報料","createTime":"2020-11-06T12:49:54.000Z","updateTime":"2020-11-06T22:20:28.000Z","uid":302236,"like":22,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":12,"replies":[{"pid":"1cdb0632fd3a0eb84575c04275453538a1e6cdcd","tid":2274493,"uid":302236,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-06T12:49:54.000Z","msg":"Hong Kong's new hotline to report breaches of the controversial national security law has received more than 1,000 calls within hours of going live.<br />\n<br />\nResidents can anonymously send in images, audio and videos if they suspect someone has violated the law.<br />\nThe law, introduced earlier this year, criminalises secession, subversion and collusion with foreign forces.<br />\nIt has already led to several arrests of activists, and has silenced protesters.<br />\n<br />\nThe maximum punishment under the law is life in prison. <span class=\"red\">Hong Kong police said they had received more than 1,000 tips via the hotline by Thursday evening, according to reports in local media.</span>Residents can submit the information via email, text or WeChat, the mainland's most popular messaging app.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-54835955\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-54835955&d=q9TyM%2Fq5ITgKOQyjXL1c9p2AEL7eB1GKmMTTK1c2%2F04%3D&h=3f866013\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-54835955&h=76b53816\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-china-54835955</a><br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"x-large\">睇嚟大家要開始block哂social media啲藍絲朋友<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />自我審查嘅迫切性又高咗</span>"},{"pid":"69bcdb0c31c7e82d30f5d78e050ccdf51e014b98","tid":2274493,"uid":302236,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-11-06T12:50:10.000Z","msg":"推"},{"pid":"90e48ea4553d9e57df9f29e8e